The correct answer is **F. \(\sqrt{2}/4\)**.

The region \(0 < |x| + |y| < 1\) is a diamond (square rotated by 45°) with area \(1\). The inequality \(2(x + y) > 1\) defines a region in the first quadrant bounded by \(x + y > 0.5\), which contributes \(\sqrt{2}/8\) to the total probability. Considering all four quadrants symmetrically, the total probability is \(\sqrt{2}/4\).

\boxed{F}
